A document delivered to the Secretary of State for filing shall be executed as follows:
If delivered by or on behalf of a corporation or foreign corporation, by:
The chairman of its board of directors, by its president, or by another of its officers;
A duly authorized representative; or
If the directors have not been selected or the corporation has not been formed, by its incorporator;
If delivered by or on behalf of a limited liability company or foreign limited liability company, by:
A manager, if management of the limited liability company or foreign limited liability company is reserved to one (1) or more managers;
A member, if management of the limited liability company or foreign limited liability company is reserved to the members;
A duly authorized representative; or
If the limited liability company or foreign limited liability company has not been formed, by its organizer;
If delivered by or on behalf of a limited partnership or foreign limited partnership, by at least one (1) general partner;
If delivered by or on behalf of a business trust or foreign business trust, by at least one (1) trustee;
If delivered by or on behalf of a partnership, by at least two (2) partners;
If delivered by or on behalf of any other entity or foreign entity, by a person certifying the authority and capacity to execute and deliver the document;
If the entity or foreign entity is in the hands of a receiver, trustee, or other court-appointed fiduciary, by that fiduciary; or
If delivered by or on behalf of a limited cooperative association or foreign limited cooperative association, by:
The chairman of its board of directors, by its president, or by another of its officers;
A duly authorized representative; or
If the directors have not been selected or the association has not been formed, by its organizer.
